<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Representation of a single sample record.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// A sample record is represented by a positive integer value, which</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// indicates how frequently was the associated line location executed.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Additionally, if the associated location contains a function call,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the record will hold a list of all the possible called targets. For</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// direct calls, this will be the exact function being invoked. For</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00323" /><CodeLine lineNumber="323"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// indirect calls (function pointers, virtual table dispatch), this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00324" /><CodeLine lineNumber="324"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// will be a list of one or more functions.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprof/samplerecord"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprof/samplerecord/#a9e45fc6fb7b892f8d86be28794da2dbd">SampleRecord</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00513" /><CodeLine lineNumber="513"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Sample context for FunctionSamples. It consists of the calling context,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00514" /><CodeLine lineNumber="514"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the function name and context state. Internally sample context is represented</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00515" /><CodeLine lineNumber="515"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// using ArrayRef, which is also the input for constructing a &#96;SampleContext&#96;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00516" /><CodeLine lineNumber="516"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// It can accept and represent both full context string as well as context-less</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00517" /><CodeLine lineNumber="517"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// function name.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00518" /><CodeLine lineNumber="518"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For a CS profile, a full context vector can look like:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00519" /><CodeLine lineNumber="519"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    &#96;main:3 &#95;Z5funcAi:1 &#95;Z8funcLeafi&#96;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00520" /><CodeLine lineNumber="520"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For a base CS profile without calling context, the context vector should only</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00521" /><CodeLine lineNumber="521"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// contain the leaf frame name.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00522" /><CodeLine lineNumber="522"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For a non-CS profile, the context vector should be empty.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00523" /><CodeLine lineNumber="523" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprof/samplecontext"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprof/samplecontext/#ab8ff16dff4a4304435e512fa6bd1066b">SampleContext</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
